<hr data-start="1413" data-end="1416">
<h2 data-start="1418" data-end="1459">✅ STEP 4: Fix VS Code Terminal Profile</h2>
<p data-start="1461" data-end="1480">Now in <strong data-start="1468" data-end="1479">VS Code</strong>:</p>
<ol data-start="1482" data-end="1624">
<li data-start="1482" data-end="1523">
<p data-start="1485" data-end="1523">Go to <strong data-start="1491" data-end="1503">Terminal</strong> → <strong data-start="1506" data-end="1522">New Terminal</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1524" data-end="1581">
<p data-start="1527" data-end="1581">Click <strong data-start="1533" data-end="1551">Dropdown Arrow</strong> → <strong data-start="1554" data-end="1580">Select Default Profile</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1582" data-end="1624">
<p data-start="1585" data-end="1624">Choose <strong data-start="1592" data-end="1602">Ubuntu</strong> (or manually add it).</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="1626" data-end="1680">⚙️ If you want to manually configure in settings.json:</p>
<ol data-start="1682" data-end="1786">
<li data-start="1682" data-end="1761">
<p data-start="1685" data-end="1761">Press <code data-start="1691" data-end="1705">Ctrl+Shift+P</code> → type <strong data-start="1713" data-end="1752">“Preferences: Open Settings (JSON)”</strong> → Enter.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1762" data-end="1786">
<p data-start="1765" data-end="1786">Add this to the JSON:</p>
</li>
</ol>
