a-start="13" data-end="29">slow it down</strong> and be <strong data-start="37" data-end="51">100% clear</strong> for you now.<br data-start="64" data-end="67">
I’ll explain it like you’re beside me, <strong data-start="106" data-end="122">step by step</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="125" data-end="128">
<h2 data-start="130" data-end="187">✅ <strong data-start="135" data-end="187">Where exactly should you type bash/wsl commands?</strong></h2>
<h3 data-start="189" data-end="262">👉 <strong data-start="196" data-end="262">You should type them in either of these two places on Windows:</strong></h3>
<h3 data-start="264" data-end="306">📌 <strong data-start="271" data-end="306">1. Windows Command Prompt (CMD)</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="307" data-end="403">
<li data-start="307" data-end="403">
<p data-start="309" data-end="325"><strong data-start="309" data-end="325">How to open:</strong></p>
<ol data-start="328" data-end="403">
<li data-start="328" data-end="350">
<p data-start="331" data-end="350">Press <code data-start="337" data-end="350">Windows key</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="353" data-end="370">
<p data-start="356" data-end="370">Type <strong data-start="361" data-end="370">“cmd”</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="373" data-end="400">
<p data-start="376" data-end="400">Click <strong data-start="382" data-end="400">Command Prompt</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="404" data-end="412">Example:</p>
