    </span><span><span class="hljs-attr">"Ubuntu"</span></span><span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-punctuation">{</span></span><span>
        </span><span><span class="hljs-attr">"path"</span></span><span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"C:\\WINDOWS\\System32\\wsl.exe"</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-punctuation">}</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-punctuation">}</span></span><span>
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="1326" data-end="1329">
<h3 data-start="1331" data-end="1384">⚠️ <strong data-start="1338" data-end="1384">What to do if you don’t see Ubuntu listed:</strong></h3>
<ol data-start="1385" data-end="1573">
<li data-start="1385" data-end="1463">
<p data-start="1388" data-end="1463"><strong data-start="1388" data-end="1463">Make sure you have closed and reopened VS Code after installing Ubuntu.</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1464" data-end="1527">
<p data-start="1467" data-end="1527">✅ Open CMD, type <code data-start="1484" data-end="1489">wsl</code> → Confirm you can enter Ubuntu there.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1528" data-end="1573">
<p data-start="1531" data-end="1573">After that, VS Code <strong data-start="1551" data-end="1561">should</strong> pick it up.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="1575" data-end="1578">
<h3 data-start="1580" data-end="1606">✅ <strong data-start="1586" data-end="1606">Summary for you:</strong></h3>
