<hr data-start="89" data-end="92">
<h3 data-start="94" data-end="161">✅ <strong data-start="100" data-end="161">Why you’re seeing “terminated with exit code” in VS Code:</strong></h3>
<p data-start="162" data-end="189">It usually happens because:</p>
<ol data-start="190" data-end="383">
<li data-start="190" data-end="267">
<p data-start="193" data-end="267"><strong data-start="193" data-end="263">VS Code is trying to open Ubuntu, but the profile is misconfigured</strong>, or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="268" data-end="383">
<p data-start="271" data-end="383"><strong data-start="271" data-end="314">VS Code is using an invalid Ubuntu name</strong> like <code data-start="320" data-end="335">"ubuntu-22.0"</code> instead of <code data-start="347" data-end="363">"Ubuntu-22.04"</code> or just <code data-start="372" data-end="382">"Ubuntu"</code>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="385" data-end="428">We’ll fix it <strong data-start="398" data-end="414">step by step</strong> properly now.</p>
<hr data-start="430" data-end="433">
<h2 data-start="435" data-end="469">⚙ <strong data-start="440" data-end="469">COMPLETE FIX STEP BY STEP</strong></h2>
<h3 data-start="471" data-end="538">✅ <strong data-start="477" data-end="538">STEP 1: Confirm the correct name of your installed Ubuntu</strong></h3>
<p data-start="539" data-end="576">You’ve already done this. You showed:</p>
