-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-5" data-message-model-slug="gpt-4o"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark"><p data-start="0" data-end="63">Great question — when your submission checker says things like:</p>
<blockquote data-start="65" data-end="191">
<p data-start="67" data-end="191">✅ “Check for the Presence of schedule.html”<br data-start="110" data-end="113">
✅ “Check Main Content and Table Structure”<br data-start="157" data-end="160">
✅ “Verify Footer Consistency”</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="193" data-end="304"><strong data-start="193" data-end="234">even though you followed instructions</strong>, it usually means <strong data-start="253" data-end="303">one or more of these issues might be happening</strong>:</p>
<hr data-start="306" data-end="309">
<h2 data-start="311" data-end="345">✅ <strong data-start="316" data-end="345">Possible Problems &amp; Fixes</strong></h2>
<h3 data-start="347" data-end="407">1️⃣ <strong data-start="355" data-end="407">schedule.html File Missing or in Wrong Directory</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="408" data-end="498">
<li data-start="408" data-end="498">
<p data-start="410" data-end="498">Make sure <code data-start="420" data-end="435">schedule.html</code> <strong data-start="436" data-end="471">is inside the correct directory</strong> in your GitHub repository:</p>
</li>
</ul>
