<p data-start="567" data-end="675"><strong data-start="567" data-end="574">Fix</strong>: Check in your <strong data-start="590" data-end="630">GitHub repository → techcon_website/</strong> to see if <strong data-start="641" data-end="658">schedule.html</strong> is really there.</p>
<hr data-start="677" data-end="680">
<h3 data-start="682" data-end="707">2️⃣ <strong data-start="690" data-end="707">Filename Typo</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="708" data-end="795">
<li data-start="708" data-end="792">
<p data-start="710" data-end="792">The file <strong data-start="719" data-end="727">must</strong> be named <strong data-start="737" data-end="748">exactly</strong> <code data-start="749" data-end="764">schedule.html</code> (all lowercase, no spaces).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="796" data-end="854">Example of mistakes:<br>
❌ <code data-start="819" data-end="834">Schedule.html</code><br data-start="834" data-end="837">
❌ <code data-start="839" data-end="854">schedule.HTML</code></p>
<hr data-start="856" data-end="859">
<h3 data-start="861" data-end="920">3️⃣ <strong data-start="869" data-end="920">Table Missing <code data-start="885" data-end="896">&lt;caption&gt;</code> OR <code data-start="900" data-end="918">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;</code></strong></h3>
<ul data-start="921" data-end="972">
<li data-start="921" data-end="972">
<p data-start="923" data-end="972"><strong data-start="923" data-end="953">The checker is very strict</strong> on HTML structure.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="974" data-end="986">Check these:</p>
