    </span><span><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">table</span></span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-attr">border</span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"1"</span></span><span>&gt;
        </span><span><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">caption</span></span></span><span>&gt;Detailed Schedule of Events for TechCon 2024</span><span><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-name">caption</span></span></span><span>&gt;
        ...
    </span><span><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-name">table</span></span></span><span>&gt;
</span><span><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-name">main</span></span></span><span>&gt;
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="745" data-end="748">
<h3 data-start="750" data-end="784">2️⃣ <strong data-start="758" data-end="784">Table Border Attribute</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="785" data-end="952">
<li data-start="785" data-end="884">
<p data-start="787" data-end="884">Using <code data-start="793" data-end="805">border="1"</code> is <strong data-start="809" data-end="821">old HTML</strong>. Some modern linters/checkers <strong data-start="852" data-end="883">dislike inline <code data-start="869" data-end="881">border="1"</code></strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="885" data-end="952">
<p data-start="887" data-end="952">It’s better to <strong data-start="902" data-end="930">remove it for validation</strong> or use <strong data-start="938" data-end="951">CSS later</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="954" data-end="981"><strong data-start="954" data-end="981">Fix (optional for now):</strong></p>
