-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark"><p data-start="0" data-end="72">Thank you for your clarity — let’s solve this properly <strong data-start="55" data-end="71">step-by-step</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="74" data-end="169">From what you’ve described, <strong data-start="102" data-end="134">the checker is very specific</strong> about <em data-start="141" data-end="154">exact words</em> and structure.</p>
<h3 data-start="171" data-end="215">✅ <strong data-start="177" data-end="215">Likely Reason for Checker Failure:</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="216" data-end="478">
<li data-start="216" data-end="373">
<p data-start="218" data-end="373">**It’s NOT “copywriter” — they meant “copyright” — meaning your HTML needs to <strong data-start="296" data-end="310">explicitly</strong> use the word <code data-start="324" data-end="337">"copyright"</code> in full lowercase or proper casing.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="374" data-end="475">
<p data-start="376" data-end="475">Sometimes <strong data-start="386" data-end="454">checkers require the word <code data-start="414" data-end="425">copyright</code> to be in lowercase exactly</strong>, or specific format:</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="479" data-end="482">
<h3 data-start="484" data-end="541">✅ <strong data-start="490" data-end="541">FINAL Version: Checker-Friendly <code data-start="524" data-end="539">schedule.html</code></strong></h3>
