<blockquote data-start="66" data-end="133">
<p data-start="68" data-end="133"><strong data-start="68" data-end="133">"Starting VS Code in WSL (Ubuntu-22.04): Downloading server…"</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<h3 data-start="135" data-end="166">✅ <strong data-start="141" data-end="166">Cause of the Problem:</strong></h3>
<p data-start="167" data-end="319">Even though you’ve connected to WSL <strong data-start="203" data-end="235">(Ujunwa [WSL: Ubuntu-22.04])</strong>, VS Code <strong data-start="245" data-end="313">can’t fully open because it needs to download the VS Code Server</strong>, and:</p>
<ol data-start="320" data-end="450">
<li data-start="320" data-end="396">
<p data-start="323" data-end="396">Your <strong data-start="328" data-end="364">WSL doesn’t have internet access</strong> to download the VS Code Server.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="397" data-end="450">
<p data-start="400" data-end="450">That’s why it’s stuck on <strong data-start="425" data-end="450">“Downloading server…”</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="452" data-end="455">
