slug="gpt-4o"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark"><p data-start="0" data-end="142">Thanks for sharing that — <strong data-start="26" data-end="68">what you are seeing is normal behavior</strong> when you run <code data-start="82" data-end="99">ping google.com</code> in Ubuntu <strong data-start="110" data-end="141">unless you stop it manually</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-start="144" data-end="171">⚙ <strong data-start="150" data-end="171">What’s happening?</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="172" data-end="291">
<li data-start="172" data-end="244">
<p data-start="174" data-end="244">The <code data-start="178" data-end="184">ping</code> command keeps running <strong data-start="207" data-end="234">indefinitely by default</strong> in Linux.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="245" data-end="291">
<p data-start="247" data-end="291">That’s why it keeps printing new lines with:</p>
</li>
</ul>
