This project is part of the HTML &amp; CSS curriculum at ALX Software Engineering.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## Objectives</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Apply advanced CSS styling techniques to create responsive and visually appealing web pages.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Implement a web design using a provided Figma prototype.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Practice the use of positioning, grid, flexbox, transitions, and responsive media queries.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Ensure W3C-compliant HTML and CSS code.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## Resources</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Figma Design File**</span></span><span>: [</span><span><span class="hljs-string">View in Figma</span></span><span>](</span><span><span class="hljs-link">https://www.figma.com/file/KCSbYso8BbsJsTUEG3rACa/alx_html_css?type=design&amp;node-id=0-1&amp;mode=design</span></span><span>)
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Images**</span></span><span>: [</span><span><span class="hljs-string">Download Images Here</span></span><span>](</span><span><span class="hljs-link">https://github.com/alx-tools/0x02-CSS_advanced/tree/main/images</span></span><span>)
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Fonts**</span></span><span>:
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">  -</span></span><span> [</span><span><span class="hljs-string">Source Sans Pro</span></span><span>](</span><span><span class="hljs-link">https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Source+Sans+Pro</span></span><span>)
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">  -</span></span><span> [</span><span><span class="hljs-string">Spin Cycle OT</span></span><span>](</span><span><span class="hljs-link">https://www.fonts.com/font/spin-cycle-ot</span></span><span>)

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## Project Requirements</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> All files end with a new line
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Must have a README.md file
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Use </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**only**</span></span><span> HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (no frameworks)
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Must validate using W3C-Validator

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## Author</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Your Name**</span></span><span> | GitHub: [</span><span><span class="hljs-string">@YourGitHubUsername</span></span><span>](</span><span><span class="hljs-link">https://github.com/YourGitHubUsername</span></span><span>)
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="1805" data-end="1808">
<h2 data-start="1810" data-end="1860">✅ <strong data-start="1815" data-end="1860">4️⃣ index.html File (Base Starting Point)</strong></h2>
<p data-start="1862" data-end="1954">ALX usually provides a <strong data-start="1885" data-end="1910">starter HTML template</strong> in their <strong data-start="1920" data-end="1940">“HTML, advanced”</strong> concept page.</p>
<p data-start="1956" data-end="2059">➡ <strong data-start="1958" data-end="2059">If you want, I can provide a starter <code data-start="1997" data-end="2009">index.html</code> based on ALX projects if you don’t have it yet.</strong></p>
<p data-start="2061" data-end="2087">Example starter structure:</p>
