<hr data-start="115" data-end="118">
<h2 data-start="120" data-end="138">✅ PREREQUISITES</h2>
<p data-start="139" data-end="167">Before you begin, make sure:</p>
<ul data-start="168" data-end="313">
<li data-start="168" data-end="203">
<p data-start="170" data-end="203">✅ You have <strong data-start="181" data-end="192">VS Code</strong> installed.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="204" data-end="235">
<p data-start="206" data-end="235">✅ You have <strong data-start="217" data-end="224">Git</strong> installed.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="236" data-end="270">
<p data-start="238" data-end="270">✅ You have a <strong data-start="251" data-end="269">GitHub account</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="271" data-end="313">
<p data-start="273" data-end="313">✅ You are <strong data-start="283" data-end="312">connected to the internet</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="315" data-end="318">
<h2 data-start="320" data-end="365">🔧 STEP 1: Configure Git (first time only)</h2>
<p data-start="367" data-end="434">Open your <strong data-start="377" data-end="397">VS Code Terminal</strong> or Command Prompt (Windows) and run:</p>
