</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="546" data-end="636">🔁 Replace with your <strong data-start="567" data-end="597">real GitHub name and email</strong> (same one used to sign up for GitHub).</p>
<hr data-start="638" data-end="641">
<h2 data-start="643" data-end="703">🔧 STEP 2: Clone a GitHub repository (to open in VS Code)</h2>
<h3 data-start="705" data-end="752">Option A: You already have a repo on GitHub</h3>
<ol data-start="753" data-end="861">
<li data-start="753" data-end="779">
<p data-start="756" data-end="779">Go to your GitHub repo.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="780" data-end="828">
<p data-start="783" data-end="828">Click <strong data-start="789" data-end="809">"Code" → "HTTPS"</strong> and copy the link.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="829" data-end="861">
<p data-start="832" data-end="861">In your terminal or Git Bash:</p>
</li>
</ol>
