</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="1724" data-end="1727">
<h2 data-start="1729" data-end="1794">💡 STEP 4: (Optional but helpful) Sign in to GitHub in VS Code</h2>
<ol data-start="1796" data-end="2076">
<li data-start="1796" data-end="1893">
<p data-start="1799" data-end="1893">Click the <strong data-start="1809" data-end="1827">Source Control</strong> icon on the left sidebar in VS Code (or press <code data-start="1874" data-end="1892">Ctrl + Shift + G</code>)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1894" data-end="1984">
<p data-start="1897" data-end="1984">It will prompt you to sign in to GitHub. Click it and follow the steps in your browser.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1985" data-end="2076">
<p data-start="1988" data-end="2076">After signing in, you can easily <strong data-start="2021" data-end="2029">push</strong>, <strong data-start="2031" data-end="2039">pull</strong>, and <strong data-start="2045" data-end="2053">sync</strong> from VS Code directly.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="2078" data-end="2081">
