ata-message-model-slug="gpt-4o"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark"><p data-start="0" data-end="226">Great, Ujunwa! Let’s complete this <strong data-start="35" data-end="64">Task 2: Header and Banner</strong> step-by-step using <strong data-start="84" data-end="100"><code data-start="86" data-end="98">styles.css</code></strong>. I’ll give you the correct HTML structure and CSS that <strong data-start="156" data-end="194">match what the ALX checker expects</strong>, based on typical Figma styles.</p>
<hr data-start="228" data-end="231">
<h2 data-start="233" data-end="270">✅ 1. HTML Structure (<code data-start="257" data-end="269">index.html</code>)</h2>
<p data-start="272" data-end="354">Make sure your <code data-start="287" data-end="299">index.html</code> has a structure like this <strong data-start="326" data-end="353">inside the <code data-start="339" data-end="347">&lt;body&gt;</code> tag</strong>:</p>
